channel_description:
I am Tawakkul, a 50-year-old Gamarvan resident. This charming mountain village lies in the heart of Azerbaijan, and its incredible nature has beckoned generations to settle here, weaving a rich tapestry of traditions. I proudly uphold these ancestral practices.

I enjoy sharing my peaceful life with you, where clean mountain air, warm sun, and living land bestow joy and peace. May you find happiness in the simple yet profound beauty of life.

title: Simple life in the mountains! Cooking roasted duck in the oven
channel_description:
Discovering the Charm of Ukrainian Villages and Traditions Amidst Challenging Times

Dear subscribers, my passion lies in exploring and sharing the culinary gems from around the world with you. However, due to the ongoing war in Ukraine, where I currently reside, I am unable to travel abroad to film new episodes featuring international cuisine. Instead, I invite you to join me on a journey to uncover the beauty of Ukrainian villages and the richness of our traditions.

Ukraine boasts numerous picturesque villages. With their charming homes, vibrant gardens, and welcoming communities, these villages exude a distinct charm. 

A standout aspect of Ukrainian culture is our incredible culinary heritage. Stemming from the agricultural practices of our ancestors, our cuisine is a testament to the resourcefulness and creativity of our people. 

I am deeply grateful for your understanding and support during these trying times. 

Connect with us: foodaroundworld@ukr.net

If anyone says that Netflix cannot change your life, then they are lying. I first fell in love with fire cooking on my couch watching TV while procrastinating school work in college. What started as a passion for fire cooking and photography has found me doing Youtube! We post recipes three times a week with tons more on our Facebook, Instagram and blog! Come follow along!

title: Cooking oven-rolled kebab in a mountain village!
channel_description:
Hello
I am Behnaz and I live in the village with my mother. My mother and I, as well as our grandparents, were born in this village and our ancestors have lived here for 300 years. This is a summer area in the heart of the Alborz Mountains. The mountains are at war with the river and the villages are very beautiful and spectacular, and most of its inhabitants are engaged in agriculture and animal husbandry. Life in the village and in the heart of nature in old and traditional ways is far from the hustle and bustle of the city.
My mother also has a number of cows, calves, chickens and roosters that she takes care of, and I also help her with her daily chores. In addition, my mother has a very tasty handicraft that is spoken by everyone in the area.
In this channel, I have tried to show you a corner of these beauties and the pristine nature of the region, as well as the daily work of myself and my mother, which I hope you enjoy watching and accompanying and supporting us.

title: Breakfast Fry Up | Over The Fire Cooking by Derek Wolf
channel_title: Over The Fire Cooking by Derek Wolf
channel_description:
If anyone says that Netflix cannot change your life, then they are lying. I first fell in love with fire cooking on my couch watching TV while procrastinating school work in college. While scrolling through the endless list of shows, I found a documentary following a South American chef and his adventures cooking with fire. It was love at first sight. I had to try it myself. When my wife and I got a fire pit as a wedding present, we decided to put it to good use. The first meal we cooked was a nice skirt steak with some homemade chimichurri sauce. It must have been beginners luck because it tasted delicious. From that moment on, I decided that if I was grilling, then I was grilling over a fire.

What started as a passion for fire cooking and photography has found me doing Youtube! We post recipes three times a week with tons more on our Facebook, Instagram and blog! Come follow along!
